wwpLayer4FilterMIB.name: wwpLayer4FilterMIB
wwpLayer4FilterMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister Postal: World Wide Packets P.O. Box 950 Veradale, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: mib.meister@worldwidepackets.com
wwpLayer4FilterMIB.description: This MIB module defines the mgmt objects to support the layer 4 filtering on the WWP products.

PortList.name: PortList
PortList.description: Each octet within this value specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'.

wwpMaxLayer4Filters.name: wwpMaxLayer4Filters
wwpMaxLayer4Filters.description: The maximum number of Layer4 Filters that this device supports.

wwpNumLayer4Filters.name: wwpNumLayer4Filters
wwpNumLayer4Filters.description: The current number of Layer4 Filters that are configured in this device.

wwpLayer4FilterTable.name: wwpLayer4FilterTable
wwpLayer4FilterTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the config parameters for the Layer 4 filter.

wwpLayer4FilterEntry.name: wwpLayer4FilterEntry
wwpLayer4FilterEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLayer4FilterTable.

wwpLayer4FilterName.name: wwpLayer4FilterName
wwpLayer4FilterName.description: The locally arbitrary, but unique identifier associated with this wwpLayer4FilterEntry.

wwpLayer4FilterProtocolNumber.name: wwpLayer4FilterProtocolNumber
wwpLayer4FilterProtocolNumber.description: The protocol number for the Layer 4 Filter. The list of protocol numbers are assigned by IANA.

wwpLayer4FilterSrcPort.name: wwpLayer4FilterSrcPort
wwpLayer4FilterSrcPort.description: The traffic addressed to the transport layer source port specified by this object will be blocked by this filter. A zero value for this object will indicate that this object should be ignored while applying the filter.

wwpLayer4FilterDstPort.name: wwpLayer4FilterDstPort
wwpLayer4FilterDstPort.description: The traffic addressed to the transport layer destination port specified by this object will be blocked by this filter. A zero value for this object will indicate that this object should be ignored while applying the filter.

wwpLayer4FilterStatus.name: wwpLayer4FilterStatus
wwpLayer4FilterStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the wwpLayer4FilterStatus column can't be set to 'active'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding instance of wwpLayer4FilterProtocol has been set. None of the objects can be modified while the value of this object is active(1).

wwpLayer4FilterAttachTable.name: wwpLayer4FilterAttachTable
wwpLayer4FilterAttachTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the attachment of created filters to the VLANs and ports. If there is no entry atached with the filter, then filter is virtually disabled.

wwpLayer4FilterAttachEntry.name: wwpLayer4FilterAttachEntry
wwpLayer4FilterAttachEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLayer4FilterAttachTable.

wwpLayer4FilterVid.name: wwpLayer4FilterVid
wwpLayer4FilterVid.description: The vlan id to be associated with this ingress filter.

wwpLayer4FilterAttachType.name: wwpLayer4FilterAttachType
wwpLayer4FilterAttachType.description: The attach type for this filter. Setting this object to 'allow' will allow the traffic specified by the filter name.

wwpLayer4FilterPortList.name: wwpLayer4FilterPortList
wwpLayer4FilterPortList.description: The set of ports on which this filter is to be applied.

wwpLayer4FilterCounterId.name: wwpLayer4FilterCounterId
wwpLayer4FilterCounterId.description: The stats related to this filter will be stored in the counter specified by this object.

wwpLayer4FilterCount.name: wwpLayer4FilterCount
wwpLayer4FilterCount.description: The stats value in the counter specified by the wwpLayer4FilterCounterId.

wwpLayer4FilterAttachStatus.name: wwpLayer4FilterAttachStatus
wwpLayer4FilterAttachStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. Until instances of all corresponding columns are appropriately configured, the value of the corresponding instance of the wwpLayer4FilterStatus column can't be set to 'active'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding instance of wwpLayer4FilterPortList has been set. None of the objects can be modified while the value of this object is active(1).
